name: Red Banks
description: Rote runde Backsteinbanks ca. 1.50 m hoch, Bänke usw.

name: Kunstwerk
description: Marmorcurb, von beiden Seiten fahrbar, wird nach hinten hin höher.

name: Flatland
description: Soweit ich informiert bin fahren hier die Flatlander, allerdings kenn ich mich da nicht wirklich aus.

name: Wallride
description:
ziemlich Steiler Wallride mit etwas stressiger Anfahrt (Fahnenmasten im Weg)
...ja, genau da unter den Bäumen :-)

name: Schlossplatz
description: Lange gewachste Beton(?)curb ca. 30-40 cm hoch. Meistens ist hier tagsüber ziemlich viel los (sprich: Fußgänger im Weg.)

name: Palast
description: Der beste Platz um Bier zu trinken im Sommer :-)

name: Blumenbeet
description: Kleine Transition aus Pflastersteinen ca 40 cm hoch

name: Liederhalle
description: verschiedene Curbs die Treppen runter, bin aber nicht sicher ob Die noch fahrbar sind, da (zumindest eine Zeit lang) Skatestopper dran waren...

name: Skatepark
description: Gurkiger kleiner Concrete Rudolph Skatepark mit Minirampe, Quarter und anderem (meiner meinung nicht wirklich fahrbarem) Gedöns.

name: Südheimer Platz
description: Hier gibts eine Menge Schräg in den Boden eingelassene Marmorplatten (sollen normalerweise die Straße vom Platz abtrennen) die man als Jumpramp verwenden kann, allerdings nur ca 20 cm hoch.

name: Hall Eleven
description: Die einzige überdachte Minirampe die ich kenne in Stuttgart. Es gibt auch noch einen Indoor Skatepark hier, allerdings nur für Skateboard, kein BMX

name: Skatepark
description: Kleiner Skatepark, war noch nie dort, soll aber laut aussage meiner Freunde, ( die Skateboard fahren) ganz lustig sein.

name: Skatepark + Racestrecke?
description: Keine Ahnung was das genau ist, habs nur mal kurz aus dem Auto gesehen, aber scheint mit ne RaceStrecke mit nem kleinen Betonskatepark zu sein.

name: Scharnhausen Skatepark
description: Ziemlich guter Betonskatepark mit halbem Bowl und so weiter, sieht man ja hier. Meistens viele Skateboarder da. Ansonsten noch ein Beachvolleyballfeld, Fussballplatz und so weiter, man kann auf jeden Fall angenehm seien Zeit hier verbringen. Angeblich gibt es in dem neu gebauten Stadtteil im Anschluss an den Park einige Streetspots, allerdings kann ich dazu noch nichts sagen.

name: Oberesslingen Skatepark
description: Der einzige Park hier in der Gegend der auch bei Regen Fahrbar ist. Beton Bowl, Minirampe, Streetfläche aus Holz. Lohnt sich...

name: Skatepark
description: Ziemlich guter Holz-Skatepark auf 2 Ebenen, mit dem BMX wie ich finde allerdings etwas stressig weil die Rampen recht nahe beieinander Stehen.

name: Skatepark
description:
Kleiner Skatepark mit einer Metallquarter,
einer Betonfunbox mit curb, zwei Grindboxen und einer verdammt steieln Bank. Klingt nach nix besonderem, aber wo kann man schon wenn man grade nicht fährt Mädels beim Beachvolleyballspielen zuschauen? :-)

name: Stadthalle
description: mehrere Metalcurbs, von beiden Seiten fahrbar, und ein paar lange flache stufensets. DerHausmeister wird euch hassen...

name: skatepark
description: Schmale minirampe, Quarter mit 90° Kurve und jumpbox mit sinnlosen ca 10 cm hohen rails.

name: Skatepark
description: War noch nie da, sieht aber von hier oben nicht schlecht aus :-)

name: DB
description: Hier gibt es ne Steincurb, abschüssig ein  5er Set runter für Leute die auf der linken Seite grinden, ums Eck noch einige kleinere Curbs und kurze Handrails die allerdings glaube ich eher was für Skateboarder sind.

name: Wassergap
description: ziemlich weites gap von einer Erhöhung über ein Wasserbecken, weiß gar nicht ob das überhaupt noch fahrbar ist, da hier früher andauernd securities da waren.

name: überdachter Flatlandspot
description: Eine Passage, hier fahren die Flatlander wenns regnet manchmal.

name: Pflastersteintransition
description: Transition aus (wie gesagt :-) Pflastersteinen ca. 50 cm hoch, war hier noch nie mit dem Rad, daher kann ich nichts zur Fahrbarkeit sagen.

name: Rathaus
description: 3er Stufenset und ne kleine gewachste Curb.

name: Schräglage
description: Die beste (weil einizige) Surferbar auf einer Dachterrasse im 5 Stock, im Sommer gibts gegrilltes, sehr angenehm dort...

name: Molins de Rei
description: R1 | R4 -> Molins de Rei

description: R5 | R6 | L1 | L8 -> L'Hospitalet-Av. Carrilet

name: Sagrada Hubba
description: L2 | L5 -> Sagrada Familia, L4 | L5 -> Verdaguer

name: Red Flat + Up and Over Ledge
Bergonier

description: Metro D Station Camara de Gaia

name: Fellbach Schwimmbad
description: Super Big street place with big red sculpture u can skate. plus more curbs.

name: Schwabenlandhalle
description: Big place good flat and long perfect crubs.

name: Staatsgalerie Stuttgart
description: Warning. U get Kicked out fast. But give it a try if u down for stairs, rails..

name: Kriegsberg
description: Bit a rougher flat. with round manual pads. plus one slappy thing.

name: St. Maria Kirche
description: curbs sponsored by NewBalance and Adidas.

name: Schlossplatz
description: Big Sculpture. with curved curb. plus stairs.

name: Geschwister-Scholl-Schule Tübingen
description: WHO Banks Steep and Rough. Asphalt banks with gib steal railing on top. There are also Some fun lil donwhills. only skate on Sat/Son.

name: Anlagenpark
description: somewhere around this area is asick gap over stair and rail. or u can use the rail. its at a parking lot.

name: MiniRamp/Vert
description: There is a little mini like 2.5m high and also a big vert ramp like 5 m high. i dont remember. but both got strange surface. its bending when um ride ^^but some can master it. so can u?

name: horns curb
description: dis is a super fun street curb. its already been used really good. when u roll on the big flat its so cool! so have fun!

name: Sparkassen Carré
description: super big flat. big wheelie/curb square also some lill botanic gap ^^peace

name: Mensa Hubba
description: 7stair with two hubbas. (just go in satilite mode :P )

name: Manny pad undercover
description: somewhere around this area is a big (45cm) and long (dunno maybe 5m) manny pad check it out.

name: Theodor-Heuss-Schule
description: good curbs somewhere undercover there but its a really hit and run game here u never know .... watch out and only skate on sunday. enjoy.

name: Südwest Flatrails
description: about 3 lil flatrails with good ground. And a Short lil Ledge/Curb/u can use it as a liil manny thing check it out :)

name: Achalm-Curb
description: Thin Pop Out Rail, Plus nearby is a Stairs to Downhill.

name: Skatepark Reutlingen
description: Good Skatepark With big bowl to snakerun with spin situation. also 3 solid curbs. some lil Bump to rail in the park. and sometimes a lot of peaple sitting on the curbs... it in the middle of the city. but cool!.

name: manny pad
description: there is a 2 stair up and 3strai down mann pad or u can up down from the top.. i hope its there :P

name: steigkirche
description:
big flat with 3 stairs and small curb.
kickout 9/10

name: Skatepark Pragfriedhof
description: Indoor Skateplaza with big bowl area and good flat plus crubs, rail, 2 block gap.

name: SLS Skatepark
description: L2 -> Badalona Pompeu Fabra, R1 -> Montgat

name: De Pomar Skatepark
description: B4 | B7 | B25 | B27 -> Riera de Canyadó - Bronze

name: Soulac Skatepark
description: Pass your way, to bad skatepark ��

description: Métro C Forum Maia

name: stuttpark
description:
super perfect 750m2 indoor park!!
check out www.stuttpark.net

name: Sirop d'érable skateshop
description: New petit shop d'un ami.

name: MACBA
description:
Metro: L1/L2 Universitat, L3 Catalunya
Spot: Long granite ledges, up ledge and stairs. Skating on Sunday and Tuesday all day and in the evenings after 7 pm which is when most people are there.

name: MACBA Big 3
description:
Metro: L1/L2 Universitat, L3 Catalunya
Spot: Excellent runway and smooth slightly inclined landing. Right behind MACBA.

name: Besos Bumps
description:
Metro: L4 Besos
Spot: The oldest skatepark in Barcelona. Smooth transition and launch at the end over a rail.

name: Besos Flatbars
description: Metro: L4 BesosSpot: If you watch for the passes that go over the freeway on your way to the Besos Bumps you might find some nice flatbars like these. Watch out for traffic.

name: Yellow Rail Road
description:
Metro: R5/R6/L8/S4/S8 from Placa Espanya to Almeda
Spot: Slightly out of the way and getting a bit worn but still worth checking out. Flatbars of different sizes and nice ledges to grind. Ground is smooth as silk...

name: Forum Brick Waves
description: Metro Station: L4 El Maresme ForumSpot: These famous huge brick waves are right down by the ocean. However be warned that there are large gaps in between each brick which makes this a challenge.

name: Forum Metal Out Ledges
description: Metro Station: L4 El Maresme ForumSpot: Famous metal out ledges.

name: Forum Snake Ledge 1
description:
Metro Station: L4 El Maresme Forum
Spot: Three snake ledges in the same area. Smooth ground with curved and straight ledges.

name: Sants
description:
Metro Stations: L5/L3 Sants Estacio
Spot: Granite benches, metal bench, metal up bench, three stairs. Parts are covered with a roof.

name: Sants Sculpture Bank
description:
Metro Stations: L5 or L3 Sants Estacio
Spot: This cool sculpture has two huge banks on both sides. The ground is a little rough but manageable. There are also some low metal ledges that go into the bank and an up ledge that is metal.

name: Sants Water Gap
description: Metro Stations: L5/L3 Sants EstacioSpot: Several water gaps

name: Barceloneta Volcano Land
description:
Metro: L4 Barceloneta
Spot: A bunch of red brick volcano's and long rounded marble pieces. The outside has ledges as well.

name: Big Barceloneta Wallride
description:
Metro: L4 Barceloneta
Spot: There are several of these on the way to the beach. Fun wall ride before heading down to the water.

Photo by Jerem Dunand (http://www.flickr.com/photos/merej/)

name: Small Barceloneta Wallride
description:
Metro: L4 Barceloneta
Spot: There are several of these on the way to the beach. Fun wall ride before heading down to the water.

name: Barceloneta Rail to Drop
description:
Metro: L4 Barceloneta
Spot: Low stainless steel rail with difficult landing.

name: Torre Agbar Hips
description: Mellow volcano hips right across from the Torre Agbar. Nice place at night because the building lights up.

name: Paral-lel Stage Ledge
description: Metro: L2/L3 Paral-lel Spot: Slight incline up to a ledge with metal coping.

name: Bari Gothica Rail Bank
description:
Metro: L4 Jaume ISpot: Smooth plaza with a few low flat bars.
<

name: Silver Rail
description:
Metro Station: L5 Horta
Spot: Stainless steel rail with down hill run up

name: Cornella Fat White Rail
description:
Metro: L5 Cornelia then take Tram T1/T2 to Fontsanto Fatjo
Spot: Fat white handrail

name: Club Natacio Flatbars
description:
Metro: L3 Drassanes or L4 Barceloneta
Spot: Low round rails

name: Round Plaza
description:
Metro: L1 Av Carrilet
Spot: 5 set, convex bank, ledges and some other fun sculpture things

name: Quarter Wall Ride
description:
Metro: L5 Can Vidalet
Spot: Famous cement quarter pipe to metal wall ride
Video: Throwaway of the Day (http://www.skateboring.net/?p=246)

name: Metal Bump
description:
Metro: L2 St. Marti
Spot: Famous thin metal bump to do launches off

name: Red Triangle Hips
description:
Metro: L2/L10 Gorg
Spot: Red brick hips by this amazing looking building.

name: Horta Plaza
description: Spot: 7 stair, several benches and rails in the area.

name: Giant Fun Slide
description: Spot: Here you will find these huge metal slides. You actually use one of them as a mini ramps. Check it out.

name: U Ledge
description:
Metro: L2 Monumental
Spot: Well waxed U ledge worth checking out.

name: Sant Roc Garbage Gap
description: Spot: Ledges down by the beach. Garbage cans at the ends to gap over. Aahhh the beach.

name: Rail to Bank
description:
Metro: L1 Torras i Bages
Spot: Famous over the rail to bank

name: La Parella
description: Metro: L4 BarcelonetaSpot: Granite out ledge with a lovely couple sitting nearby watching.

name: Zona Franca Handrail
description: Metro: L1 Santa EulaliaSpot: Stainless steel handrail

name: Sibiles-les Banks
description: Spot: Smooth banks and hips. Check out the area.

name: WTC Ledge
description: Spot: Down by the world trade centre this ledge to drop is also surrounded by a bunch of other fun little objects to skate.

name: WARNING: Ledge to Bank Heaven
description:
WARNING: Many people who have gone here recently have gotten tickets from the police. Skate at your own risk.
Metro: L5 Collblanc
Spot: Smooth downhill spot with ledge to banks over and over again. Enjoy the ride.

name: Passeig de Fabra Banks
description:
Metro: L4 Llucmajor
Spot: Big brick banks with transfers. Bank also has gaps to do tricks over

name: PCNB Yellow Brick Hip
description: Spot: Massive mellow brick hip.

name: Guano Banks
description: Spot: Sorry about the roller blader shot it was the only one I could get. Otherwise this spot is a bit rough but a great bank to grind.
